  "commentary": "**Dealer Hedging Commentary:**\n\nWith SPX at 6574.27 sitting above the GEX flip at 6557 but below the massive gamma wall at 6580 (+25.5B), dealers are in a moderate hedging position and will ramp up selling pressure as we approach 6580 where they'll need to short delta against long gamma positions. The PIN regime with heavy positive gamma concentration between 6580-6600 creates a strong magnetic pull toward 6580, suggesting any momentum toward 6590+ will face increasing dealer resistance. Watch 6580 as the critical level—failure to break above should trigger mean reversion back toward 6565-6570, while a break below 6557 flips dealers to negative gamma and removes the stabilization mechanism.",
